name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
notes:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. *** All patients 16 years old and older can register regardless of phase. (If 16-17 years old must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. Enter the building at the time of your appointment only. 
***You MUST bring proof that you live or work in WA (such as a utility bill; a voucher from your employer; or your work, school, or state ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
notes:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY FOR 1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all individuals aged 16 years & over. This will be at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Given the limited supply of COVID-19 vaccine available at this time and Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location you must either live or work, or get your medical care in Washington state.  Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided. 
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA SOLAMENTE PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA PRIMERA DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas de 16 años en adelante.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. 
Dado el suministro limitado de la vacuna COVID-19 disponible en este momento y el compromiso de Washington con el acceso equitativo y justo, aquellos que buscan vacunas para el COVID-19 en esta clínica deben vivir o trabajar, o recibir atención médica en el estado de Washington.  El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una. Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Arlington Airport Covid-19 Vaccine Site
notes:
**** THIS CLINIC IS PRIORITIZING 2ND DOSE PFIZER.  YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record). ***** 
Starting April 15, 2021, everyone 16 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination.

Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 16 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form).

Vaccination at these sites is by appointment only for those eligible in the current phase.  Be prepared to provide identification as well as appointment confirmation at check-in.  Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
